      "matchingRecords": [],
      "meetsCriteria": true,
      "result": {
        "justification": "The patient is an 80-year-old female with documented confusion and fatigue with reported increased difficulty with balance and use of a walker at home (ED note 10/27/2019, RN notes 11/23-11/24/2019). She had a recent syncope episode without fall but with risk of fall (ED note 11/22/2019, RN notes 11/23/2019). She is on aspirin 324 mg (medication list 10/27/2019) which increases bleeding risk. Labs show hypokalemia (potassium 2.3 on 11/22/2019 and 3.2 on 10/27/2019) and acute kidney injury (creatinine elevated to 1.64 on 10/27/2019 and worsening on 11/22/2019). She is on prednisone (up to 60 mg daily) and Bactrim DS for PCP prophylaxis, indicating immunosuppression (medications and ED notes). Family reports forgetfulness and vivid dreams causing confusion (ED note 10/27/2019). These factors combined increase risks for falls, bleeding, infection, and medication adherence challenges. No history of contrast reaction or implanted devices was reported (MRI screening form). These risks are important for ongoing management including fall precautions, monitoring electrolytes and renal function, infection prevention, and careful medication review.",
        "medical_risks": "Fall propensity, cognitive impairment/confusion, bleeding risk from aspirin use, hypokalemia, acute kidney injury, immunosuppression from prednisone and Bactrim use, syncope risk"
      }
    },
