            "Justification": "Document 74 is an ophthalmology note dated 2019-04-22 describing detailed lens findings, cataract types, dry eye syndrome, and surgical planning including YAG capsulotomy and cataract surgery with intraocular lens, indicating a preoperative ophthalmic evaluation.",
            "notes": "Lens exam showed 1+ PCO, 2+ NS, 1+ cortical cataract, and 1+ PSC; angles open; dry eye syndrome noted; patient planned for cataract surgery with intraocular lens implantation and YAG capsulotomy for PCO.",
            "vision_visit": "Ophthalmology exam pre-cataract surgery",
            "visit_date": "2019-04-22"
          },
          {
            "Justification": "Document 20 is a post-operative ophthalmology note dated 2019-05-03 describing day 1 post cataract surgery OS, normal tear film, optic nerve assessment, glaucoma suspect status, and intraocular lens presence, confirming a post-op follow-up visit.",
            "notes": "Post-op day 1 cataract surgery left eye with expected healing; normal tear film; cup-to-disc ratio 40; flat periphery; open angle glaucoma suspect right eye; presence of intraocular lens in both eyes.",
            "vision_visit": "Post-operative cataract surgery follow-up",
            "visit_date": "2019-05-03"
          },
          {
            "Justification": "Document 77 is an ophthalmology/optometry encounter dated 2024-06-09 describing bilateral eye redness, conjunctival injection, no discharge, normal pupils and fundus, diagnosis of blepharoconjunctivitis, and treatment prescribed, indicating an acute eye problem evaluation.",
            "notes": "Bilateral conjunctival injection with redness and itchiness; no discharge; pupils equal and reactive; funduscopic exam normal without hemorrhage; diagnosed with blepharoconjunctivitis and treated with olopatadine and polymyxin B sulf-trimethoprim eye drops.",
            "vision_visit": "Evaluation for bilateral blepharoconjunctivitis",
            "visit_date": "2024-06-09"
          }
